item.title: About Me
item.description: *At [Ginzan Onsen](http://www.japan-guide.com/e/e7975.html)* I was born February 5th, 1995. I got my bachelor's degree in Computer Science from the University of Puerto Rico at Río Piedras in early 2018. Apart from computer science and math, I enjoy studying philosophy and different languages. If you're interested in my resume, you can obtain it here.

item.title: Open Source Projects
item.description: Here are my open-source projects as well as some projects I've contributed to. noticias-pr A command-line interface for reading the latest from local news sites in Puerto Rico. Tech Highlights: NodeJS Web scraping Available on npm cc-api (Work-in-progress) An open-source API for Caribbean Cinemas. Tech Highlights: TypeScript MongoDB Web scraping vgstack (Work-in-progress) Keep track of your video game backlog. My full-stack clone of The Backloggery.
